> Info: NEED INSPIRATION?Check out our guide on building better documentation to learn best practices for creating and organizing documents in Confluence.

> Tip: Here are some tips to get you started. You can edit this page to see how it works!

## 1. Create a page

- Click "Create" and select "Blank Page" to create your first page.
- New pages are created as children of the page you are currently viewing.

## 2. Add to your page

- Click "Edit" to enter the Confluence editor and use the page layouts feature to structure your content using sections and columns.
- Use headings to format your text and drag and drop images into your page to provide visual interest.
- Click "Insert" and select "Other Macros" to add macros for navigation, special formatting and other media.

On this page:
## 3. Organise your pages

Here are some tips for organising your content.

- Change the page order

The sidebar on the left displays your pages in a hierarchy. If you have Space Administrator permissions you can click "Space Tools" > "Reorder Pages" to move pages around.

- Add labels

trator permissions you can click "Space Tools" > "Reorder Pages" to move pages around.

- Add labels

Labels help keep pages organised and make it easier for you to find the information you need. Click "Labels" at the bottom of a page to add or edit. The "Related pages" section on this page uses labels too!

- Make templates

Standardise and speed up the page creation process with templates. You can create and format a template with page layouts, standard headings and instructional text for hints and guidelines. Check out our sample page on

## 7-) E-com Shipments

E-com shipment file contains online orders. Channels of online orders are indicated by ORSOType Column. This column has three values:

- MP: Market place. Online GNC stores that are operated on Amazon, E-bay, etc. are indicated with ORSOType == MP.
- OG – Order Groove (subscription orders)Sources:  OG_STORE – order taken in store  OG_ONLINE – order taken gnc.com
- SSFC gnc.com                                                                                                                             SFCC_DOMESTIC – gnc.comSFCC_PRO - PRO Customer, signed up for x $ per year (pro box)SFCC_INTERNATIONAL – gnc.com orders shipped out of USSFCC_RESHIP – gnc.com orders reshipped from customer service

IONAL – gnc.com orders shipped out of USSFCC_RESHIP – gnc.com orders reshipped from customer service

| --- | --- | --- |

| OrderDate | String | YYYY-MM-DD format date that represents order submission date. |

| ORSOCode | String | Specific value for a sales channel. I.e. ORSOType = MP & ORSOCode = Amazon. |

Rules of sub item relations usage:

- If the items are subbed, generate forecasts for the new item and show it on the UI
- If the relationship is broken, generate forecasts for both and show both on the UI
- If the relationship is broken and one of them is discontinued, do not generate forecasts for the disco and do not show it on the UI

# How to reach when there is an issue?

## 1-Hour Solution

Apply a cap to forecast. Via UI, multiplier, freeze forecast whatever. In production, it should be an acceptable level for the customer. Inform the customer about quick patch and let them know we are investigating the underlying reason

## Permanent Solution

Understand the root cause in detail.

If it is not an actual problem:

Inform the customer and explain the reason. When they understood it, remove the “1 hour-patch solution”
